      "writtenOn": "2019-03-07T22:09:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I took a deeper look, and here is what we want to avoid vs what is allowed\n\nTry to avoid:\n\na. user opens 2 pipes and call snapshot save from both of them simultanously\n\nAllowed:\n\nb. user opens multiple pipes (for snapshot or AR);\nc. user calls snapshot on one pipe, wait for its completion, then call snapshot again on the same or different pipe;\nd. GC hasn\u0027t cleaned up the pipe before user opens a different pipe and calls snapshot\n\nI believe sSnapshotCrossSession-\u003emPipesAwaitingResponse would only have more than 1 element when (a) happens. In other situations, sSnapshotCrossSession-\u003emPipesAwaitingResponse will be cleaned up before snapshot save returns to the guest (or it won\u0027t be touched at all if no snapshot save command is sent).\n\nDoes it sound OK?",
      "parentUuid": "d357e27f_8412a4fb",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 269,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 269,
        "endChar": 70
